  <entry>
    <title>JHU Workshop Notes One: Intro to R</title>
    <url>/2020/03/03/2020-03-03-how-to-write-rmd-documents-in-hexo-system/</url>
    <content><![CDATA[<h1 id="Introduction"><a href="#Introduction" class="headerlink" title="Introduction"></a>Introduction</h1><h2 id="Termology"><a href="#Termology" class="headerlink" title="Termology"></a>Termology</h2><ul>
<li>Script; Command; Comment; Variable; Fun; Argument</li>
<li>How to put arguments into a fun?<ul>
<li>Check the help page</li>
<li>Order for arguments (not required, but recommend)</li>
<li>Know default for arguments</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Do I have to set/enter all arguments?</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="Synatax"><a href="#Synatax" class="headerlink" title="Synatax"></a>Synatax</h2><ul>
<li>A set of rules</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="Packages"><a href="#Packages" class="headerlink" title="Packages"></a>Packages</h2><ul>
<li>A collection of R funs</li>
<li>Base: function name{base}</li>
<li>Base cheat sheet<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.rstudio.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/r-cheat-sheet-3.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">http://www.rstudio.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/r-cheat-sheet-3.pdf</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Install packages<ul>
<li>Install.package()</li>
<li>Library()</li>
<li>[packagename]::[fun]   eg. devtools::check()</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Where can I find R packages?<ul>
<li>CRAN</li>
<li>Bioconduct ???</li>
<li>Github</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Most used packages<ul>
<li><a href="https://towardsdatascience.com/top-100-most-used-r-functions-on-github-9caf2b81b314" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://towardsdatascience.com/top-100-most-used-r-functions-on-github-9caf2b81b314</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="Working-directory"><a href="#Working-directory" class="headerlink" title="Working directory"></a>Working directory</h2><figure class="highlight r"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">getwd()</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<figure class="highlight plain"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">## [1] &quot;/Users/haner/Desktop/IntroToR&quot;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<figure class="highlight r"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="comment">#setwd()</span></span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<h2 id="R-project"><a href="#R-project" class="headerlink" title="R project"></a>R project</h2><ul>
<li>A collection of files (data; results; graphs)</li>
<li>To keep your analysis organized<ul>
<li>Data; papers; rcode; writing; Rproj; Readme</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Relative path: use to do reproductive work and share</li>
<li>What files do you have in this folder?<ul>
<li>.Rhistory</li>
<li>.Rproj</li>
<li>Auto-saved</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="Help-in-R"><a href="#Help-in-R" class="headerlink" title="Help in R"></a>Help in R</h2><ul>
<li>?funname</li>
<li>?”special characters”</li>
<li>help(package = “package name”)</li>
<li>example(function name)</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="Data-Type"><a href="#Data-Type" class="headerlink" title="Data Type"></a>Data Type</h2><ul>
<li>Most common atomic data type<ul>
<li>Numeric:  1, 2.3, 14.78</li>
<li>Integers</li>
<li>Complex</li>
<li>Logical</li>
<li>Characters </li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Find out the data type<ul>
<li>class(2)</li>
<li>class(4L)</li>
<li>class(1+2i)</li>
<li>class(TRUE)</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Change data type later too<ul>
<li>as.numeric()</li>
<li>Remember some cant be changed or in an error way!!!</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="Data-structure"><a href="#Data-structure" class="headerlink" title="Data structure"></a>Data structure</h2><ul>
<li>Data Frames<ul>
<li>Create a data frame</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>data.frame()</li>
<li>Load mtcars data frame<ul>
<li>data() # to see the different datasets within R</li>
<li>?mtcars</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Useful commands<ul>
<li>str() # find out the stucture of a data frame</li>
<li>head()</li>
<li>head(mtcars,10) # list the first 6 rows of data (or you could specific how many rows you want to preview) </li>
<li>tail() # list the last 6 rows of data (or you could specific how many rows you want to preview) </li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Subset<ul>
<li>[row, column]</li>
<li>[“var name”]</li>
<li>df$var<pre><code>® mtcars[3,2]
® mtcars[3, ]
® mtcars[3:7,2]
</code></pre></li>
<li>Use subset() to select data (ex: mpg &gt;15)<pre><code>® subset(mtcars, mpg &gt; 15)
</code></pre></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="Explore-data"><a href="#Explore-data" class="headerlink" title="Explore data"></a>Explore data</h2><h2 id="How-do-I-select-data"><a href="#How-do-I-select-data" class="headerlink" title="How do I select data?"></a>How do I select data?</h2><ul>
<li>subset()</li>
<li>comparision (&gt;;&lt;;&gt;=;&lt;=;==;!)</li>
<li>R logical operators<ul>
<li>!x</li>
<li>x&amp;y</li>
<li>x | y</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p>##Try yourself</p>
<figure class="highlight r"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">str(iris)</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
